						               													<description>From the back of the book:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Ethiopia 1887-1896 features 10 action-packed historical scenarios from Italy's only colonial adventure.  The Ethiopians, Italians, and the Dervish clash for control of Abyssinia and the port of Massawa.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The scenarios:&amp;#10; 1. Lt Cuomo's Advance (The Battle of Saati) - January 18, 1887&amp;#10; 2. The Dogali Fight - January 26, 1887&amp;#10; 3. The Battle of Gallabat - March 12, 1889 Dervish vs. The Ethiopians!&amp;#10; 4. The Battle ofAgordat - December 21, 1893 Dervish vs. The Italians!&amp;#10; 5. Fort Halai - December 18, 1894&amp;#10; 6. The Battle of Coatit - January 13, 1895&amp;#10; 7. Rear Guard at debra-Alia - October 9, 1895&amp;#10; 8. Amba Alagi - December 7, 1895&amp;#10; 9. The Center Brigades (Adowa) - March 1, 1896&amp;#10; 10. Dabormida's Brigade (Adowa) - March 1, 1896&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The scenarios are all organized to be played using The Sword and the Flame, but can easily be adapted to any rules set. Units are set at 8 figures instead of the traditional 20. This allows for faster play, greater flexibility and .. your one 20-figure unit becomes 2&amp;frac12; units instantly! Play on either a 6'x4' or 8'x5' table. Give it a try!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Other sections include:&amp;#10; - Uniform Information for the Italians and the Ethiopians!&amp;#10; - History of the period!&amp;#10; - Information on the Italians and Ethiopian armies!&amp;#10; - Campaign Rules!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
